cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CL

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on video understanding and spatiotemporal models. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and supervised datasets, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of synthetic rendering and 3D objects suggests a possible fit with cs.RO (Robotics), and the diagnostic tools provided for analyzing video architectures could also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
